<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Python on Kathy's Portfolio</title><link>https://KathyKo.github.io/tags/python/</link><description>Recent content in Python on Kathy's Portfolio</description><generator>Hugo -- gohugo.io</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Sat, 10 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="https://KathyKo.github.io/tags/python/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Taiwanese-Chinese Lyric Translator</title><link>https://KathyKo.github.io/p/lyric-translator/</link><pubDate>Sat, 10 Apr 2021 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://KathyKo.github.io/p/lyric-translator/</guid><description>&lt;img src="https://KathyKo.github.io/p/lyric-translator/egg.png" alt="Featured image of post Taiwanese-Chinese Lyric Translator" />&lt;h3 id="conceptualization">&lt;code>Conceptualization&lt;/code>
&lt;/h3>&lt;p>As an undergraduate student in the Taiwanese literature department, after completing the Introduction to Computing course, I began to contemplate how I could integrate coding skills with my major studies. Thus, I embarked on this small project, hoping to apply it within my field of study.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Users can choose from five songs to translate, allowing them to listen to music while learning Taiwanese simultaneously.&lt;/p>
